                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="What investigational products are available for individual patients?"
                        text="&lt;p>In general, only those investigational products that are part of existing or planned clinical trials would be considered for access under this policy. You can consult the U.S. National Institutes of Health for their&amp;nbsp;current list of &lt;a href=&quot;https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/results?term=abbvie&amp;amp;Search=Search&quot;>AbbVie’s clinical trials&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;or other local programs detailing clinical trials such as the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.clinicaltrialsregister.eu/ctr-search/search&quot;>EU Clinical Trials Register website&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>It’s important to understand that there are circumstances in which we would be unable to provide access to some of these investigational products even though they are being studied in clinical trials.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_1
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:29:24.558Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="What diseases or conditions qualify for investigational products available through AbbVie’s Pre-Approval Access pathway?"
                        text="&lt;p>In general, only conditions for which there is evidence of potential application of an investigational product that is part of existing or planned clinical trials would be considered for access under this policy. &amp;nbsp;Or the use of the requested product may be considered with justification by the product mechanism of action or by published clinical data for the disease or condition.&amp;nbsp; You can consult the U.S. National Institutes of Health for their current list of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.clinicaltrialsregister.eu/ctr-search/search&quot;>AbbVie’s clinical trials&lt;/a> or other local programs detailing clinical trials, such as the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.clinicaltrialsregister.eu/ctr-search/search&quot;>EU Clinical Trials Register website&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>It’s important to understand that there are circumstances in which we would be unable to provide access to some of these investigational products even though they are being studied in clinical trials. Such decisions are made on a case-by-case basis.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_2
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:29:48.098Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="How do I apply?"
                        text="&lt;p>We accept requests only from the doctor who is treating you for the disease or condition. Your doctor should review the above information about how to contact us.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_3
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:30:09.489Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="If I am approved, how much will it cost me? Will it be covered by my insurance or government programs?"
                        text="&lt;p>AbbVie provides products at no cost through the Pre-Approval Access pathway. However, there’s no way for us to know if there will be other costs associated with your treatment. It will depend on your insurance and many other factors. The best thing to do is talk to your doctor.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_5
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:30:32.954Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="Who reviews requests?"
                        text="&lt;p>All Pre-Approval Access requests and programs are managed within AbbVie’s research and development team. Only medical personnel can make decisions about these requests and all other AbbVie employees are specifically prohibited from having any involvement in the decision-making process.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_6
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:30:51.383Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="How can I check the status of my request?"
                        text="&lt;p>We will acknowledge receipt of the request from your doctor within two business days. We also will contact your doctor with any additional questions about the request. We are committed to make an appropriate medical decision about access to investigational products as quickly and as fairly as possible and we will notify your doctor as soon as we have reached&lt;br>a decision.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_7
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:44:01.921Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="Why was I denied?"
                        text="&lt;p>Your doctor was provided an explanation of our decision. You should discuss this with your doctor. For both medical and privacy reasons, AbbVie does not directly contact patients.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item_8
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:44:27.321Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        classes_defaultOpen="{Boolean}false"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="Why did you deny my request when there are other people with the same disease or condition as me who you approved?"
                        text="&lt;p>We consider each request individually, and no two requests are identical. In addition, because there are limited supplies of investigational products, there may simply not be enough to meet all the requests we receive.&lt;/p>"/>
                    <accordion_item
                        jcr:created="{Date}2026-06-16T15:45:39.214Z"
                        jcr:createdBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:46:04.274Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="How can I appeal your decision?"
                        text="Your physician would need to contact AbbVie to initiate an appeal. All appeals will be reviewed."/>
                    <accordion_item_424419872
                        jcr:created="{Date}2026-06-16T15:46:06.490Z"
                        jcr:createdBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-06-16T15:46:32.989Z"
                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="pratteks@adobe.com"
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        aueComponentId="accordion-item"
                        model="accordion-item"
                        modelFields="[summary@text,text@richtext,classes_defaultOpen@boolean,ariaExpandLabel@text,ariaCollapseLabel@text]"
                        name="Accordion Item"
                        summary="Because clinical trials are the primary means of access to investigational products, I’d like to consider enrolling in one. How do I do that?"
                        text="It’s important to consider the clinical trial option first, because patients who are eligible for an ongoing clinical trial do not qualify for access to investigational products under AbbVie’s policy.Each clinical trial has its own eligibility criteria, procedures and enrollment process. Please review the information on the current list of AbbVie's clinical trials by visiting the U.S. National Institutes of  Health website and the EU Clinical Trials Register website, and discuss it with your treating physician.If you and your doctor identify a clinical trial for which you might qualify, work with your doctor to begin the application process."/>
                </accordion_18>
